{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Greenland", "text_new": "{{short description|Ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic in Greenland}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = COVID-19 in Greenland\n| map1            = \n| legend1         = \n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Greenland]]\n| first_case      = [[Nuuk]]\n| arrival_date    = 16 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=3|day1=16|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = \n| recovery_cases  = 11<ref name=\"cdo\">{{cite web |title=Coronavirus-ip nutaap siaruarnera malinnaaffigiuk |url=https://nun.gl/Emner/Borgere/Coronavirus_emne/Foelg_smittespredningen |accessdate=8 April 2020 |language=da,kl}}</ref>\n| deaths          = 0\n| confirmed_cases = 11<ref name=cdo />\n| website         = \n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have spread to [[Greenland]] \u2014 an autonomous territory of the [[Kingdom of Denmark]] \u2014 in March 2020.<ref name=GLfirst/> There have been 11 confirmed cases, but none in need of hospitalization. The last infected person had recovered on 8 April and there are no known active cases in Greenland.<ref name=\"cdo\"/>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n==Timeline==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Greenland medical cases chart}}\nOn 16 March, the first case in the territory was confirmed.<ref name=GLfirst>{{Cite news|author=Redaktionen|url=https://sermitsiaq.ag/corona-alarm-afblaest-test-negativ|title=Corona-alarm afbl\u00e6st - test var negativ|date=10 March 2020|work=Sermitsiaq|access-date=10 March 2020|url-status=live|language=da}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=F\u00f8rste coronatilf\u00e6lde bekr\u00e6ftet i Gr\u00f8nland |url=https://www.dr.dk/nyheder/indland/foerste-coronatilfaelde-bekraeftet-i-groenland |website=DR |accessdate=16 March 2020 |language=da}}</ref> The first infected patient lived in the capital, [[Nuuk]], and was placed in home isolation.\n\n\"Preparations have been initiated to cope with the new situation. It is important that citizens follow our recommendations now that the infection has reached our country,\" said Greenland's Prime Minister [[Kim Kielsen]] at a press conference, according to newspaper ''Sermitsiaq''. All non-essential flights to and from Greenland, as well as domestic flights, are strongly advised against. Public gatherings of more than 100 people are discouraged and citizens returning from high-risk areas are recommended to self-isolate for two weeks.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/greenland-confirms-first-case-of-coronavirus|title=Greenland confirms first case of coronavirus|website=The Straits Times|date=16 March 2020|accessdate=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 March, the government prohibited the sale of alcoholic drinks until 15 April in Greenland.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/29/alcohol-sales-banned-in-greenland-capital-during-lockdown |title = Alcohol sales banned in Greenland capital during lockdown|newspaper = The Guardian|date = 29 March 2020|last1 = France-Presse|first1 = Agence}}</ref>\n\nAs of 9 April, there have been 11 confirmed cases, all in Nuuk, all of whom have recovered, making Greenland the only affected territory in the world to become free of COVID-19 without any deaths.<ref name=cdo />\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in Greenland|Coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic in Danish dependencies|Greenland]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in North America|Greenland]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Greenland]]\n\n\n{{Greenland-stub}}\n{{COVID-19-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic in Greenland}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = COVID-19 in Greenland\n| map1            = \n| legend1         = \n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Greenland]]\n| first_case      = [[Nuuk]]\n| arrival_date    = 16 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=3|day1=16|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = \n| recovery_cases  = 11<ref name=\"cdo\">{{cite web |title=Coronavirus-ip nutaap siaruarnera malinnaaffigiuk |url=https://nun.gl/Emner/Borgere/Coronavirus_emne/Foelg_smittespredningen |accessdate=8 April 2020 |language=da,kl}}</ref>\n| deaths          = 0\n| confirmed_cases = 11<ref name=cdo />\n| website         = \n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have spread to [[Greenland]] \u2014 an autonomous territory of the [[Kingdom of Denmark]] \u2014 in March 2020.<ref name=GLfirst/> There have been 11 confirmed cases, but none in need of hospitalization. The last infected person had recovered on 8 April and there are no known active cases in Greenland.<ref name=\"cdo\"/>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n==Timeline==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Greenland medical cases chart}}\nOn 16 March, the first case in the territory was confirmed.<ref name=GLfirst>{{Cite news|author=Redaktionen|url=https://sermitsiaq.ag/corona-alarm-afblaest-test-negativ|title=Corona-alarm afbl\u00e6st - test var negativ|date=10 March 2020|work=Sermitsiaq|access-date=10 March 2020|url-status=live|language=da}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=F\u00f8rste coronatilf\u00e6lde bekr\u00e6ftet i Gr\u00f8nland |url=https://www.dr.dk/nyheder/indland/foerste-coronatilfaelde-bekraeftet-i-groenland |website=DR |accessdate=16 March 2020 |language=da}}</ref> The first infected patient lived in the capital, [[Nuuk]], and was placed in home isolation.\n\n\"Preparations have been initiated to cope with the new situation. It is important that citizens follow our recommendations now that the infection has reached our country,\" said Greenland's Prime Minister [[Kim Kielsen]] at a press conference, according to newspaper ''Sermitsiaq''. All non-essential flights to and from Greenland, as well as domestic flights, are strongly advised against. Public gatherings of more than 100 people are discouraged and citizens returning from high-risk areas are recommended to self-isolate for two weeks.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/greenland-confirms-first-case-of-coronavirus|title=Greenland confirms first case of coronavirus|website=The Straits Times|date=16 March 2020|accessdate=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 March, the government prohibited the sale of alcoholic drinks until 15 April in Greenland.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/29/alcohol-sales-banned-in-greenland-capital-during-lockdown |title = Alcohol sales banned in Greenland capital during lockdown|newspaper = The Guardian|date = 29 March 2020|last1 = France-Presse|first1 = Agence}}</ref>\n\nAs of 9 April, there have been 11 confirmed cases, all in Nuuk, all of whom had recovered, making Greenland the only affected territory in the world that solved the problem with Coronavirus cases without any deaths.<ref name=cdo />\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in Greenland|Coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic in Danish dependencies|Greenland]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in North America|Greenland]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Greenland]]\n\n\n{{Greenland-stub}}\n{{COVID-19-stub}}\n", "name_user": "IceTigress", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Greenland"}
{"title_page": "Alain Pointet", "text_new": "{{short description|Olympic sailor from France}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox sailor\n| name           = Alain Pointet<ref name=\"Sports-Reference\" />\n| image          = \n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| native_name    = \n| birth_name     =  \n| fullname       = \n| nickname       = \n| nationality    = {{FRA}}\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1959|11|19|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Neuilly-sur-Seine]]\n| death_date     = yes but date Unknown\n| death_place    = Unknown\n| height         = {{convert|1.82|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n| weight         = \n| classes        = [[Soling]]\n| club           = [[Trinite sur Mer]]\n| collegeteam    = \n| coach          = \n| medaltemplates = \n| show-medals    = \n| updated        = 29 February 2020\n}}\n\n'''Alain Pointet''' (born: 4 February 1957, Death date unknown) is a sailor from [[Neuilly-sur-Seine]], [[France]]. who represented his country at the [[Sailing at the 1992 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling|1992 Summer Olympics]] in [[Barcelona]], [[Spain]] as crew member in the [[Soling]]. With helmsman [[Marc Bouet]] and fellow crew member [[Alain Pointet]] they took the 15th place.<ref name=\"OS1992\" /> \n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs =\n  <ref name = Sports-Reference>{{cite web\n                                  |url        = https://web.archive.org/web/20121107094645/http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/po/alain-pointet-1.html\n                                  |title      = Alain Pointet Bio, Stats, and Results \n                                  |publisher  = Sports-Reference.com \n                                  |work       = Olympic Sports \n                                  |accessdate = 29 February 2020 \n                                  |url-status = live\n                                  |df=dmy \n                                }}</ref>\n  <ref name = OS1992>{{cite web\n                        | url        = https://di